<article class="post-body container">

<h1 class="post-h1">“It Sold… Now Where Is It?”</h1>

<p class="post-lead">
Every reseller has this moment.
You hear the cha-ching notification…
and suddenly you have no idea where the item is.
</p>

<p>
The problem isn’t storage space.
It’s the system.
</p>

<h2>The real issue</h2>

<p>
Most resellers store items in real places:
closets, totes, shelves, spare rooms.
But the tracking system lives somewhere else —
spreadsheets, notes apps, memory.
</p>

<p>
That disconnect is what creates the panic.
</p>

</article>